{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid462989\charrsid16072257 {\*\xmlclose}
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid462989 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I wonder if you could start by telling me about your earliest memories of your life. What's the very first thing you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The first think I can remember is having my food there. I don't remember going because I was a baby in long clothes when I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You were taken as a baby, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, taken in as a baby, and I c
an remember then ... I think I was about 3 when I can really remember. And I remember sitting round a table having a meal and I couldn't eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What they call skilly, it was just milk and stuff. And the matron - and I think the nam
e was Lockey then, she lived there with her father. Her mother was dead, and she used to take me into her private room and give me little bits of something there, something. I was a favourite somehow or other, why I don't know. I was a cripple, you see, a
nd my toes were where my heels were and I couldn't get about very well, but I had to get about so I got about. And then I don't remember much 'till we were boarded out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Tell me again, when she used to take you into her room, what sort of things did she give you to eat there, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, it was ... sometimes she'd give me potato, the lunchtime, you see ... potato and a little food ... meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Because the skilly consisted of milk and what else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Skilly. I don't know what it was, but I've never liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Is it like a kind of soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was just like thin milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No meat in it, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No nourishment, seemed like it, in it. She'd take me in there and she'd give me, perhaps, a jam tart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you feel fond of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I loved her. She was the daughter of the man, you see. She wasn't the wife, the wife was dead. The daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Of the man who ran it, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was acting as matron. And he was the master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was he like, do you remember him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't remember much about him. I didn't ever come in contact with him much, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what other grownups were there there, supervising? At the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I couldn't say, only ... you see, I was more ... I was with the children And the
re were old people there. They used to take bad girls in there, you know, naughty girls ... women. There was a woman from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St.{\*\xmlclose} Osyth named Ong }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ... was in there, and she was put in there because she was ... her parents couldn't do anything with her. And t
here was another one called Polly Smith, well she taught us our lessons, the alphabet, I remember. We used to sit on a straight-backed stool ... no back to it .. a plain form, to have our lessons ... A B C, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you like learning your A B C?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I was always fond of learning, I loved it. I should've liked to have ... well, If I'd had the means I would have done better with my life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember where you slept when you were in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dring {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}? Did all the children sleep together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I can't remember, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you mix at all with these older people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, we were kept by ourselves, the children. Yes, the children were in a room my themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can you remember any other children there, that you got friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I don't remember them. No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can you remember anything else about being there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Not exactly about being there, but I remember the day I came away. It stands out in my memory, because we all stood in a row, like thi
s you know, and we had our ... I had a cloak, a cloak with a cape to it, brown, and black hat, shiny straw with red ribbon, and a pair of brown shoes. And we stood in a row ready to go, for the Union van to take us. But the strange thing about it was I di
dn't go in a Union van, I wasn't put in then. I began to feel a bit frigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
ed to think all the others were going and I was left. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 But they kept me back because the matron and master took me in their private cart ... a little high cart, because there were no
 motors those days.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Why do you think you were kept back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, I think they thought they'd like to take me, you see, and see where I was going. I don't know, they seemed to have taken an interest in me and I never knew why. Maybe it's because I 
was a cripple, you see. They took me to this foster mother's in this high dog cart.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Now when you left there to go to your foster mother's, how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I think I was between 3 and 4. I could remember ... just remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Had you met the foster mother before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I'd never seen her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Had they prepared you for where you were going? I mean, had they told you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I don't think they did, I never remember. They just took me round the house and I was invited in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 And that was from Tendring to Gt. Bentley, the journey?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 Tend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
ring Institution, it's ... I don't know whether you've seen it, it's a big place. Of course, mind you, it's so much altered today. It was ... well, they treated you just anyhow there, you see. But I was very fortunate, as I say, why I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Because of the interest the matron took in you, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She took such an interest in me, yes, and I think she was a sweet woman. I think that was a lot of it. I think she had a nice nature.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you went to the foster mother, can you remember your arrival there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I was very frigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ed. I hadn't been told a thing, you see. And when I got in there was a little ... there was a fire - it was winter - time - there w
as a chair, a little chair in front of the fire and this lady asked me to sit in it. She said, 'sit down', and I did and she gave me some biscuits, but I remember I couldn't eat them ... didn't eat them, 'cos I was too upset, couldn't think where I was. A
n
d after they discussed had been talking and they said they were going, I got up to go, thinking I was going back with Matron and Master, but I didn't. I had to stop. So I cried, I said, 'I don't want to stop here I want to go back to my other home'. I rem
e
mber as if it was yesterday. And I was a little ... very, very frail. Frail little thing, white face, and they cropped my hair like a boy. They all had to do it ... they all had to have it done, the children. It was to keep it clean, you see, so when I ca
me to Bentley I'd got short hair like a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did the other children remark on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Some of them did, but they were very good. They weren't too bad. But the foster mother always made me wear a cap, and I could never understand that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And why do you think it was? Because of the short hair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, I think so, yes. Because I had pretty hair after, when it did grow. I had wavy hair and I didn't have to do anything to it, it was very, very nice. But of course, I've had a lot of bad illness and I haven't got any hair now, hardly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When your hair grew again, did she let you stop wearing the cap after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010  Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 es, oh, yes, after a time, yes. Of course, I went straight to school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 As soon as you arrived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 As soon as I arrived,
 yes, first day. And I came home at lunchtime, I'd had enough. And the school then was here, at the Methodist Chapel, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Weslyan{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Day School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well then, that was in 1896 they built the one that's there at the station, 'cos I remember coming out of school h
ere watching them build that. After school was over here, we used to trot along and have a look. And of course, that was a board school, then. But then it went to a Council school, didn't it? And now it's a preparatory school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Primary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So when you got to your foster parents' it was in the morning, was it? Or was it in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, it was the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So it was the very next day you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Went straight to school, yes. And the cousin took me ... well, she would be a niece, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Of the foster ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Of the foster mother, yes. She took me, but I come home at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}}11 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, but I had to go back. But they were very kind ... my teacher was. She was a Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Meacher}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 . She married a Mr. Dowman, a
fter. And she was most kind and considerate. She knew I was a cripple and she never blamed me, but I wasn't late, but I was a bit slow. But she was very, very sweet with me, always, even 'till - well, I knew her 'till she died. She still lived in Gt. Bent
ley all my life and I was always fond of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
And when you went to that school the first day, do you remember anything about it, how it struck you? 'Cos it was your first time you'd been to a school, really, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, we sat on ... there wa
s a gallery there, and we sat on the gallery, and nobody spoke to me and I didn't speak to anybody. They were very ... you see, if you come out of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
 it's a stigma. They tell you. I had it said to me, 'I'm not playing with you, you come out of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}'.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was that said to you of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 by children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They would do it of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  yes, but as time went on it wore off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What about the other grown-ups in the village, did you feel they blamed you for coming out of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Union{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Not the grownups, th
ey were very kind to me in the village, the people were. They were very kind. I think they were sorry for me, but I was such a wee little thing. And one person said, 'Mrs. Herbert, she won't keep that child, she won't get better', but the doctor said, 'if
 I come to Gt. Bentley', Dr. Athill, he said, 'she'll get on. The air is what she wants', and I did get on. It took a long time, but I got on all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you get less air when you were in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}? Were you indoors more there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, yes, yes. Yes, you were shut in more. And I went out every day in the air, do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Tell me about your life with the foster parents. Did you have a lot of duties to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't, 'cos I went to school, you see, but I had to do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you got home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Home from school. And in the morning, early morning ... I should think I was a little older then, I should say I was between 6 and 7 then, I had to go down to a farm and get the milk, at 7 in the morning. She gav
e me a cup of tea before I went but I had my breakfast when I came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How long was the walk to the farm to get the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I ... it's a long way, I can't explain it to you. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Eden
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s Farm, it's called. Mr. Lord lives there now. And if he hadn'
t any milk I had to go to his relations another ... further on, round another corner. It's a long way to go, and sometimes my hands were blue. I had to take the neighbours' cans as well as Mother's, you see. And they were some of them thin, they cut my fi
n
gers. But the woman where I went for milk, she used to give me a bun or an apple. She was ever so kind. People have been very kind. I don't know why, what it was that made them like that. But they were very kind to me, and you must speak if people are kin
d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you used to do this long walk to the farms, what time did you get back to have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I had to get back by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}half past 7{\*\xmlclose}, a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 45}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}quarter to 8
{\*\xmlclose} I had to get back. Then I'd have my breakfast and go off to school. I come home dinner
time and have to run to the shop again. Every day when I come home there's always the shopping to do. And then her mother lived ... well, about as far as, I should say ... where can I say? You don't know the directions about here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I know some places, but not very many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Past Mr. Tooley's, past the ... oh, up to the vicarage, I should think - quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The old vicarage or the new vicarage now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, the one here, just here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where the vicar lives now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Well, I used to hav
e to sleep with her mother because her mother lived alone. She was getting on. In a thatched cottage, right across the other side of the green. Straight across that way. Because the foster parents lived down that way and I had to come straight up like tha
t to ... I always called her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They lived down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Thorrington}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5727481\charrsid10629010  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, did they? Down that direction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, down the road that leads ... do you know where Mr. ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was it round De Vere }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Estate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  way, that direction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Not De Vere, the Birch Abbey Estate. That's by the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That's where the foster parents were, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, they lived further ... straight down on the other road. The Grandma lived on the same ... you just had to go straight to a corner. And I had to sleep with he
r because she was alone, and it was very dark, but I had to go up every night, and I didn't like going up in the dark. And so the foster father ... I liked him, I always got on well with him. He used to take my part on the quiet if he thought ... she was 
angry with me he wouldn't let her be angry. I was punished of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 when I really didn't do anything. It wasn't my fault, you see. But anyway, I was afraid to be naughty. I wouldn't be naughty, I was afraid. And I used to have to go up there, pitch dark in the
 wintertime, and I used to be so afraid, and I sat like that. And I think of the foster father, used to sit opposite me I think he used to think, 'she's thinking she's got to go up there alone, I'm sure she is'. I know he had that thought. He used to go t
o the gate just before I'd got to go. And when I got to the gate he'd say}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Now you take and run, I'll stop here 'till you come back', you see. I didn't mind going then. And in those days men got drunk, because the public houses were open all day, and there w
as a man's house that I had to pass that I didn't like because he was always drunk, and I used to meet him sometimes, you see. That terrified me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have a light to take with you on your walk up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. There were no torches then. No, no. No l
antern, I didn't have. Oh, no, I had to go in the dark. And I've always had that feeling, I do now, in the dark, somebody's just going to touch me on my back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You think it started at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I do, I think that's what did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you got to the grandmother's house, what did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 . She was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She lived all on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, all on her own. She had a bad knee, and I remember the foster mother saying to me, 'when you go, you open that door. You can if y
ou like', she said, 'don't make her get up with that bad knee'. Well, I couldn't reach it. It was the latch - if you know what a latch is - not a knob. Well, I couldn't reach it, I was such a little mite. But I had to call her, and she came. I said, '}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
', she said 'what's up?' I said, 'don't tell Mother you opened the door for me, will you? She told me I wasn't to ask you'. 'Don't you worry about that, dear'. She didn't tell her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was she the mother of the foster mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Foster mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did they get on well, the mother and the daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, she got on well with her, yes. And I did her shopping, poor old lady, and she used to say, 'there'll be a penny change and you get some nice rock, and bring}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010  it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 '. And I'd bring it home, I 
wouldn't touch it. Wouldn't look at it, or even ... wouldn't take a piece, I daren't. Not even for anybody. I wouldn't do such a thing. And she'd give me a piece and she said, 'you know where that is, she said, 'you leave that here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you used to spend the night there, did you go from her house to school in the morning, or did you go back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I ... I had to light her fire. The foster mother said, 'you light }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 
Granny's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  fire before you come', and I was only a wee mite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What age were you when you had to start going to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Granny\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I should think I was about 7.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you had to light the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
, to 7. I used to light the fire, and then go home and have my breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 At the time that you went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 Granny\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  house and had to light her fire, did you also have to go and get the milk, as well, at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, but I used to get up and go there, then go down and get the milk and come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So you must have had to get up quite early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I did get up early, oh, yes. But sometimes I didn't have to go, because there was a dairy opposite, a Mr. Newman, his father kept it. And I used to go there for milk, but you see when they hadn't got the milk, that's when I had to go to the farm. I didn'
t always have to go because sometimes they'd got it. Mr. Newman had got plenty. I only just had to go over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And can you tell me something about the little boy that the foster parents had? You said they had a son, didn't you? What was his name?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Percy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And how did you get on with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, all right. But, you know, she made so much difference, naturally, I suppose, she would for her own. But she'd be backing cakes on Saturday and he could sit in the room with her while she baked the
m, and I was sent outside to chop the big box of wood. And I knew, I'd got it in me .. I wasn't silly. I thought, 'yes, you're eating cakes, and I'm out here'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 do that sort of thing to you, make you feel different from him? Did it happen quite of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, she was very hard on me at times. Very. And I know ... there won't be no names mentioned in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I promise you. After all, your name's not on it, either, is it? No, I promise you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, nor her name, nor the boy
's name. Dad used to give us a penny Saturdays, and I had one as well, and I used to go and get my pennyworth of sweets - we had a quarter 1b. for a penny in those days, nice lot we had for a penny - and he used to get his. Well, perhaps ... and I was nev
er a girl to eat up anything and I don't now. I keep things, sometimes, and I have to throw them out. I just have one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 and I don't want any more. Well, I had my sweets on the Saturday, like that and I'd have some, perhaps, for Sunday morning, or Monday,
 and she'd say, 'what are you eating?' 'oh, one of my sweets'. 'Sweets?' Where did you get them from, then?' 'well, 'He said, 'I bought them on Saturday.' She'd say, 'well, give him one, then', you see. 'Course, I had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, she of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  hit me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where would she hit you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She'd hit you on your hands, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, on me bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With her hand, or with a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. No, she never had a cane. Then she used to put me on the stairs in the dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 As a punishment, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did that frigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  you a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I didn't like it. And I know Father used to come home - 'where's Kate?' 'Oh, on the stairs! 'Open that door, Percy, let her out' 'She's not coming out and don
't you open that door!' 'Well', he says, 'there's always this when I come home, 'he said, 'now you let her out! Come on, sit up and get your tea and leave off crying,' I was sobbing. 'Course, I couldn't stop it. She'd say, 'that's her temper!' I can hear 
her saying that now. 'That's her temper, make her cry'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think it worried him a lot that she used to treat you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, he didn't like it. He said he wouldn't come home if she kept on like that. He said, 'I won't come home,' he said, 'I'll keep at work'.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How long would she keep you on the stairs like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 An hour or so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
But when he come home, you see, I came out. He said, 'Now get your tea and don't keep crying'. 'Let her alone', she says, 'leave her alone and let her get on with it'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she ever punish her own son, or was she very indulgent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I've never seen her hit him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of work did the foster father do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, he worked for Mrs. Gibbons at The Lodge. He was a gardener. He was there 23 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did he ever take you out with him, on outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, they used ... he used to go for a walk Sunday nights, and he used to go through the cornfields. We used to like that, and I always went, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You and the other boy, you both went?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we both went. We weren't allowed to play on Sundays, we had a reverent Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Tell me about your Sunday, how it went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We got up in the morning, went to Sunday School at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}}10 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. We came home, if we didn't stop there 
'Till 11, then we went to Chapel right next door. We came home and had lunch - I had to change me dress. I mustn't go to Sunday School in that Sunday dress, the velvet dress. Had to change me dress. After we had dinner we went to Sunday School. We came ho
me from Sunday School, we weren't allowed to go for a walk or play on Sunday, we had to go home. And if it was cold, or anything like that, I went to Chapel at night. The boy didn't, I was sent to Chapel alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 All on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. But if it was
 nice, Father would say, 'We'll all go for a walk tonight. Would you like to go in the fields?' Well, of course, we used to say 'yes' and we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you say you used to start the day with a Sunday School? Your first service was a Sunday School, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Sunday School at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}}10 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So you'd have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Sunday{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Schools{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  Chapels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Methodist{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was to get me out of the way, I expect, I don't know. I used to wonder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And Percy didn't have to go to those, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 He didn't go to so many, but he did go to the Sunday School in the afternoon, and to Chapel in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you say that you had a special velvet dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I had a red velvet dress, and it was piped with black ribbon, narrow baby velvet ribbon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you like it very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, and when I sat down I picked it up. I didn't sit on it, I mustn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I remember the dress you described that your foster mother got you in your essay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Ah, yes, that wasn't a dress, that was a coat. She went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 and got that for me, and it was a pretty ... and I looked ... I did, I was such a dainty little thing. And, of course, the poke bonnet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You must have been a nice child to dress, really, to dress up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I dress, you know, I felt it, and I wouldn't make it dirty. Always very, very careful. And that had to come off ... I don't know what she did with it, she must have sold it, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think that she felt sort of pleased when she dressed you like that? Did she get any pleasure from dressing you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, I think she liked to see ... she thought that the people in the village'd think, you see, she'd been making a fuse of me. I think that's what it was for, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think she was criticized at all by people in the village for her treatment of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, she kept herself to herself. Oh, no. Nobody knew anything about it, she was very reserved and very Victorian. Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What things about her, do you think, were very Victorian?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, she never mixed, for one thing. She wouldn't go to a shop. I did the shopping. She never neighboured, she'd just speak, perhaps, but nobody ever went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And she never went in to other people's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't think she ever went in a shop. She'd go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 and do a big shopping on the Friday, or Saturday. Mostly on a Friday, I remember, 'cos she used to get the joint. And she'd buy a picnic ham, I always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, and she used to do it ..
. to pack up for Father for dinner, 'cos he always came home ... we always had a hot tea. She kept a good table, I will say that. Good food, wholesome food, and meat puddings. And she was spotlessly clean. Spotless. Yes, she'd got her good points. And she
 could make a shilling do when people spend }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
. Wonderful manager, she was. On the corner - I can see it, now - a sheet of foolscap and she'd put down every day what she'd spent, and on the Saturday she tabled it up. That was put on the fire and a fresh one put up for the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think her husband handed over all his money to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, he never let her go short. He was a good husband. He was a good husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was she a local person, had she been born and bred in Bentley?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, not in Gt. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 Bentley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , but St. Osyth. I think she was born at St. Osyth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she have many relatives of her own? Did you meet many aunts and uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, she had a sister that I remember. Oh, and she was sweet. She used to take my part in lots of ways, Aunt Alice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember any other outings or festivities of any kind at that time, when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, we used to have ... we had lamb sale on the green, you know, every year, and they had a wagon on the middle of the green for the 
auctioneer to stand in, and they used to come overnight, some of these poor sheep ... hot weather. And they used to ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 Granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
, as I say, lived at the corner and the sheep were right in the front on the green, and they of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5727481\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 used to come to hers for a pail of water. And she used to make tea. Now, Mother used to go up to her mother's and make tea on lamb sale day and they used to come and buy it - a cup of tea and a cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did they pay for it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I couldn't tell you. I should
 say about a penny a cup of tea and a halfpenny a cake. They wouldn't charge any more than that. That would be about the price, 'cos as I put in that bit of paper, things were so cheap then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there lots of people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, they came from all over the place, and they used to come round selling cherries and sweets a day from school, we had a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time of the year would it be, then? June or July?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 July, yes, say July or August, something like that. I should say more like Jul
y, yes, 'cos we'd have been on holiday if it had been August and we had a day off from school, I remember, so it would be more like July.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did they have any entertainments, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, no entertainments, no. And it was on all d
ay, and there was a big marquee where the ... not the drovers ... the farmers had their lunch. A proper lunch, they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Who would have provided that lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The people from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}. I don't know whether it was 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Tweed{\*\xmlclose}, or Last, or ... I wouldn't think they would be about then. I would be somebody before them, 'cos they're later, aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Tweed{\*\xmlclose} and Last, they're in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester
{\*\xmlclose} now ... caterers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What about Sunday School outings, did you have any parties or picnics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 N
o, we didn't. I'll tell you what we did have, was school treats. Sunday school treats. And we all met at the Weslyan Sunday School here, had our best clothes on, and we all carried a mug. That was to be for the tea. We had to take our own mugs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 A mug from your own home, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes. And we had a Gt. Bentley brass band. We were in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 s, we marched down, we all had a Union }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 J}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 ack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  on a stick and we used to march from the Chapel round to the signpost ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That signpost on t
he green, there. Well, we walked there and then we went across the grass to where Mr. George Wright lives, Moorlands. You know where the new nursing home is, where Jack Wright lives now? Well, we went across there, and there's a house right down in the co
rner and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 little cottages further on. Well, we went straight down to that big house and in through the stackyard on to a lovely meadow, and that's where we played for the whole afternoon. We had tea, there were trestles all up; mothers could go, and we ran
 races. I won a workbox, I remember, so it shows you how better I got with my feet. I won a workbox.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How old would you have been about then, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't know, 8 or 9. I should think 8 or 9. And I went to school and I would keep at Sund
ay School if I went to the other school. I went to school 'till I was 20 because I taught the Sunday School children. I didn't leave Sunday School when I left day school. I kept on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What age were you when you started teaching at the Sunday School instead of being a pupil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .... I was 20, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You started being a teacher at 20, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I'd got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 classes to take.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But when you first started teaching Sunday School how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I don't think I was ... well, you see, I was in a class 'till I was nearly 20.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was that unusual, or at that time was it quite usual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, that's what they did, if they could get a girl that they thought would suit, they would take her and ask her to teach. And I had }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  classes, we were short of teachers, but we had ... we had a hundred in our Sunday School. A lovely Sunday School.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was it bigger than the Church of England Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, this was the Methodist Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I wondered which was the bigger of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  in the village then. Was there a Church of England one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, the Methodist was the biggest, far the biggest, yes. And the better school, they were taught better. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How many children were there in your own class when you used to teach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I had 20, quite 20. No, more than 20, 'cos I'd got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  classes into one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you like teaching then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I loved it, and they were very pleased ... they liked me, I'm sure they did. And I used to buy them texts and give them and write the
m one out and they were to learn that for next Sunday, and then I'd give them another new text I'd bought in the shops, you know, a pretty one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you buy them out of your own money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And how of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  did you go to Sunday School through that time, twice a day - Sunday - right through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, only once in the afternoon they had a big Sunday School. The morning class was ... a little old chap took that on his own, you see, that wasn't that was a Sunday school, but you didn't get the marks like you did in the afternoon, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did most of the children go to the afternoon one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, there was a lot in the afternoon ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But did you keep on in the morning one, too, right up until you were 20? Or did you stop the morning one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't. Oh, no, I stopped the morning one and I went out to work, you see, at 14. You couldn't get away in the mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, of course not, no. Did you know anything about your parents, or how you came to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I knew my mother's mother - my grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And your mother died, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I can show it to you, I think I've got it. As near as that, I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They told you she died when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, that's hearsay. I never saw me father. That's my Grandma, you can see a likeness there, the square jaw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, there's definitely a likeness, isn't there? The shape of the face and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, you wouldn't mistake it. She was a dear ... she was a Sunday School teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Walton-on-the-Na}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 e. Yes, that was a little, tiny one and I sent it up in a newspaper ... they were doing them for an advert, and I thought, 'well I'll get that enlarged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Done very well, isn't it. But you didn't know anything about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Nobody ever told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, they are on the birth certificate. All I know was he was ... Mother's name was Sarah Sparrow ... formerly, Sarah Bailey, formerly Sarah Sparrow, and his was George Bailey, and he was a journeyman carpenter. That's all I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you ever ask people about him, or wonder about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But I had a sister, she went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, and I saw her when she was, I should think about 22 ... 25 to 30.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you hadn't seen her until then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
And she used to write to me at one time, but then she never wrote and I never heard, oh, for years and nobody's ever heard anything of her. Don't know whether she got killed in the War, or ... never heard. And I had a brother, Bert, he'd got }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  sets of teeth at the top and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  at the bottom and he wouldn't have them out. And he was deaf. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 doctors didn't pass him for service, but the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 th one did and he was out in the Army }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  weeks and he got killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the First World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And h
e'd promised me a home, he'd always promised me a home. And when he joined up he wrote me and said he would be on a certain train passing through Gt. Bentley and I went over and I stood on the platform, and he waved me good-bye. It's the last I saw of him
, in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  weeks he was gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was that the First War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, the first World War, yes. And he promised me a home. And I had another brother, he was married, lived in Walton, and he died I should think, about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years ago. They never acknowledged me, none of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But the sister did write to you for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She wrote to me, yes, and I saw her in Walton when I went and saw Grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How much older were these brothers and sisters than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, they were a lot older than I was. I w
as the baby, you see. And I did hear that Grandmother took the other children when Mother died, but me she couldn't take. I was so delicate she put me in a home, you see. She put me in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 Ten}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dring Institution. That's how I came there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you think about your brothers and sisters a lot when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I didn't know then, when I was a child, much about it. I learnt afterwards, you see. But I've got a niece, she comes once a year to see me from Walton. Me brother that died about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years ago, that was her father, and nobody had wr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 itten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 to me 'till she wrote and said, 'Dear Auntie, I thought you would like to know you're the last of the family'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And she comes to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Once a year she comes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But you never saw the others at all frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I never ... they never bothered about me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And the grandmother, did you ever see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, and she was very deaf, stone deaf, she would shout. She fell down and broke her thigh and then she got that set with a pinion and then she fell down later and broke the other, so that took her off. I went to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when did you first meet her, your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I went to her house in Walton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were you grown up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, I was old then. She 
kept the Victory Inn at Walton and I went down there a few weeks back with my foster niece and her little girl, that is her, and I said to her, 'I'll show you where auntie used to live, where Auntie's Grandma lived, dear, look' and we looked up and they'v
e had all the Victory done up beautifully. It's nice. And I said, 'that was the bedroom I was born in, I was always told. The end bedroom'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But while you were actually a child you didn't see her or any other relations?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. Well, I did see an aunt and an uncle from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. How old was I? I don't know ... I couldn't have been about 10 or 11, and Father had been to a rummage sale a week or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  before at the Church and he'd bought me a lovely cradle, doll's cradle. It was the vicar's daughter's. And at
 the Christmas time before he bought me a doll from the shop, for Christmas, so I used to ... I never played with it. I never had it to play with. And my aunt and uncle wrote and said they were coming from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I'd never seen them, they'd never seen me,
 and they came to the foster house, and I can remember coming out of school and I'd got me best dress on; she'd dressed me up ready for when I come out of school, and this doll laid in the pram ... in the cradle. That was put there to look at, I never had
 it. And I never saw that from that day to this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Put on for show, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, put on for show, much as to say we'd got some toys, but I never had it, and I never had it after that, so I don't know what happened to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Shut up somewhere, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Give away, or sold, or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And do you remember meeting them, how you felt? Were you excited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I felt .. they were just like strangers to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were they friendly to you, did they put you at your ease?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, they were all right with me, yes, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It didn't mean anything, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Just like strangers. I didn't feel I wanted anything to do with them, you see. I'd never seen them before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you ever see them again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, they never come any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Why do you think they came, then, just to have a look at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 That's what they came for and I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 think they'd've come again if she'd invited them, but she didn't. She let them see she didn't want them, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I see, she didn't make them at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She wouldn't make them comfortable. They had their tea and then they went off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have any holidays? Go away for a holiday when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. We went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} once a year when we had our month's holiday from school. You
 know you have August - it's mostly a month we used to have. Well, I remember we used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} ... I had to save my money. I used to run errands for people and had 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 d. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 a week, for ... she took that 2d. I never had any sweets or anything with it. It
 was put in a mug in the cupboard ... she'd got some cup hooks, and it was hung on one of those and her boy's was hung on the other. One was a Jubilee cup and the other one was a Coronation cup. I well remember. And I counted my money one day, we were all
 
hitting there, and I couldn't make my money right. Couldn't make it right. And Percy kept laughing, and Mother didn't make any comment on it. I said, 'well, somebody's had my money. I put it all in there, and there isn't so much. There's some of it gone. 
N
ever said any more about it 'till Father come home, and I said, 'somebody's had my money out of my mug', he said, 'don't be silly', I said, 'well, I haven't got it, and I had more than Percy 'cos I run errands and he doesn't' And the boy sat there laughin
g
. So he said, 'Know anything about it, Maria?' That was Mother's name, you see. So she said, 'I don't know what she's talking about'. I said, 'My money is gone. Mrs. Taylor gave me 2d. yesterday and I put that in'. And so Father said, 'Have you took her m
oney?' He said, 'she's got her money'. He said, 'Have you took her money?' and he burst out laughing, and he said, 'Get your cup down here ... your mug down here. Now then, 'he said,' you give her that money back'. He had taken it out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And was he punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. But I'm not going to say he did it. He may have done it for a bit of barney. But that wasn't nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And if he hadn't taken your part you probably wouldn't have got it back, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I may not have done. Yes, we went out to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} and I remember one day
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Carry on telling me about when you went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} one day and Auntie came and her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  children, a boy and a girl and Mother went into a shop and bought a coat. We all went in; and she got outside
 and bought a hat, I should say, and she left her coat. When she got outside she said, 'Ooh, I've lost me coat'. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 said - Aunt Alice said, 'did you pick it up?' She said, I don't know whether I did, and she was walking all the time she was saying it, s
o I said, 'I'll go and see.' I was like that, I didn't mind what I did for anybody, as a little child I would. I came out and when I got out I took the wrong turning, so I got lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you find them again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, but if was very late and I can't 
think how it was that Father came down. I think it was that he'd promised to come down by a later train. And anyway, he came and hunted about and he found me and when we got to the station the train was in and the gate were crossed and they wouldn't let m
e
 come through with Dad. So Mother had to go home without Father and I. But she stood at the carriage door, she saw us, she knew I was found. So Father said, 'Well, we shall have to get on the next train'. 'Well, he asked the porter if the train stopped at
 Gt. Bentley, the next one. He said, 'yes'. Well it didn't and it took us through to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So he said, 'we'll obviously go to Aunt Ellen's'. That's his sister. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Leinster Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and we went there and stopped the night.
 And when I got off the train down to the station the porter gave me some strawberries. I don't know where he got them from. And it was early in the morning, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, 'cos I'd got to come to school. So we got the train home in the morning and I went stra
ight home and went to school. It was all over the village, Kate Bailey was lost. All over the village, it soon got round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And was your foster-mother very worried, do you think? Because I suppose she didn't have a telephone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, that was her fault, really. She didn't say much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you enjoy staying the night in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}? Was it nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, I didn't like it. I'd never seen the people before, you see. Everybody seemed strange to me. I'd never seen his sister, Father's sister - that was Father's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She didn't come and visit at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Never used to come, no. No. Mind you, I tell you, she was so Victorian nobody would - and if they did they never come a second time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 'Cos they weren't made to feel comfortable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They weren't made comfortable, weren't made welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you went on this visit to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} was it a sort of annual event?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, we always went once a year, you see, and I saved my money to pay my train fare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was what the money was saved for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the club, you see, and a little to spend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How much money ... I mean how long did you have to save for to pay the fares?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I saved a lot. I didn't have all my money I saved. I used to run errands for different people a
nd I always took my money home and give it to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And how much money did people give in those days to a girl who ran errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I went 2d. a week, entered a shop for a week for 2d. And now I was doing the other neighbours' as well and my fa
ther sometimes saw me struggling along across the green with a big basket and that and he didn't like it. He said that was bigger than I was, the basket. He said, 'well, who've you been shopping for, then?' and on the order was some ... on the paper was t
he order for a Mrs. Creswell and a Mrs. Woods and Mrs. Taylor. I'd been shopping for all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And so she would give you 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 . and you'd do the shopping for her neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, and I didn't know I was doing ... So Father stopped it. He said, 'you're not going'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So you didn't do any errands after that, then, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So did you have any other means of earning a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 pocket money}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. Didn't have any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So that was your source of money gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, an
d the penny I had a ... Dad always gave me a penny every Saturday, and there used to be a show come to the Lion, a man with some ... like, puppets only they weren't puppets then, they were little things he'd got. It was a penny on an afternoon, a Saturday
 afternoon. He used to give me a penny to go there, Dad did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. They played 'The Babes in The Wood' and you could see the leaves covering up the babies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did they do 'Punch and Judy'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, it wasn't a 'Punch and Judy', it was ... there was a man named Dartnell, Mr. Crotchet and Mr. Dartnell and they were both lame.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And they had the puppets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They were like puppets. They ... the birds were on wires, you see, and the little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 robins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , and they'd open their beaks, you see, and pick up the leaves. I expect they were worked at the back by something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They had a little theatre, did they, on a stand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, that's very nice. They called it Timbertoe. Called Timbertoe. They said, 'Oh, Timbertoe is coming this 
afternoon', and we'd go, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They had it in the open air, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, in The Lion, in The Lion. They'd got a big room, with a big window, you can see it from here, a huge window. Well, there's a big room and we used to go, all the children in the village used to go, nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And they played the Dulcimer for music, you know, with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  hammers. Oh, every now and again, not very of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did they do any other things besides the 'Babes in The Wood'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It didn't last very long, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, but it was nice. You see, there was nothing doing about here, otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there any other kind of concerts or anything like that, do you remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, there were fairs used to come here, and I remember the Dell's wild beast show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
There were wild beasts in cages. And one day I thought I'd be very ... well, I don't know whether I thought I was very clever, but the front of Butcher Law ... Butcher ... what's his name, the butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Jowrie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Jowrie! They'd got a dead horse they'd killed or bought and cutting it up for this animals, and I stood there and watched then cut it up and I can't understand how I could stand and watch them feed the lions. Then
 there was a fair. They used to have fairs here. Fairs every year. Nice fairs; all kind of stalls; rock stall; coconut shies; swing-boats; horses going round and round and it used to be packed! Mother and Father used to go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How long would it stop for when it came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 A week, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what about the games you were telling me you used to play, can you tell me about them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, we used to play games that we all used to play together. Our friends named Gosling and some named }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 Cowell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
, boys and girls all got together and we put some stakes in a ring and tie a string round and that was our ring, the circus ring. Well, I'd do some skipping; the Foster brother, he'd stand on his head; the other Foster brother ... well, I don't think he w
as ... yes he was. Well, he was 17 years after the other. He was born ... he wasn't born 'till 17 years after his other brother and there was none in between, so I can hardly think that was him, he wouldn't be the younger one. Well, the other boy would ri
de a bicycle backwards. Do things like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You'd have your own little circus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, we had, yes. And then we played ball. Then we played knuckles, sit on the grass. The grass was lovely, and we'd sit on the grass and play knuckles - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  stone. And then we played with marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The girls played marbles, too, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, but we played knuckle with marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How do you play knuckle, can you tell me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You throw them up. You throw one up and scramble up 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Before the other one comes down, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 And then we played German Oneses and German Twoses, they called it.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That is, that's when you throw them you up. Then there was dropsy, you picked up one and dropped one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean there are a lot of different things you do with different names in the game, is that it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And do you do it as a competition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, we just played. There's no competition, but we just played. Then we'd go like that and put the marbles
 here and we'd shoot one in there and in there, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In between your spread out fingers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Then we'd throw them up and catch the lot. I of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  say sometimes I believe I could play it if I'd got the marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was knuckles originally played with knuckle bones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't know. No, I don't ... never met that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You only ever saw it played with marbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With marbles, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what about the game of marbles itself, did you ever play that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, you had a hole in the ground and you throw see if you can get it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And do you try and knock anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, you knock somebody else. They throw one up, then you throw one .. yours, and you try and knock his out of the way. And sometimes you do good for him, yo
u knock it in the hole for him, but you should mind that. That's what you should mind you don't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And can he win your marbles away from you? Did they play it like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, you had to give him the marble if he won.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How would he win, though? If you knocked his away and you got in, would you take his marble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, you take that marble, yes. Sometimes you'd finish up with none. Then you have another game and try and ... you get some more if you ... but you couldn't have any of those, you
'd lost those, your pal had got those, he'd won them. If you'd got some more you could start another game and go off again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you get back the ones he'd won? Would you ever get them back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. Perhaps if you win them back you got them, but if you didn't win you never got them. And they were 14 a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What about hopscotch, did you play that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. I mustn't play hopscotch. Kicked the toes out of me shoes, I wasn't allowed to ... oh, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You weren't allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, oh, no. She'd ... when I come home from school she'd look at my toes see if I'd been ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were you the only child that wasn't allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Had to stand and watch them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were all the other children allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. I wasn't. I had to stand there and watch them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what other games? Did you ever play at imitating foxes and hounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, on the green, but I wasn't allowed to play. Percy did, the boys. They used to jump in the ditches and they used to shout' 'loo, 'loo, 'loo' when the fox was caught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 One of the boys pretended to be the fox, did he?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did only boys play that game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, they did here, yes, they played it a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Not girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, not ... no, they didn't of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And any other kind of games that you used to play, can you remember? Did you skip a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we used to skip, but I wasn't allowed to skip, but I used to do it on the sly. I'd take me shoes off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You enjoyed skipping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I loved it, but I wasn't allowed t
o, you see, I was afraid I should be watched. If I went to the shop she'd be looking through the window, see how long I'd be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She'd check up on you, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can you tell me a little bit more about school, the lessons, the kind 
of lessons you learnt and what sort of subjects you had in school? When you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We had just the ordinary sums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you do it on a slate or in an exercise book?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, we had slates. We had slates then. We had slates and then, of cour
se, there was the certain days the board men came in and we had to recite to them. The vicar came in. I had to get up - it was always me - I had to get up and recite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of things did you recite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 "The Pipes of Lucknow" was one, and the - 
what do you call it? The "Half a league, half a league, half a league onward ...". What is that, now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 By }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
nyson? "The Charge of The Light Brigade"?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That's the one. Used to get that one. Had that to recite once, I remember. Ooh, that's a long one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you like reciting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Is that why they chose you, 'cos you did well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What's the one about Lucknow? I don't know that one. Who is that by, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How does the first line go, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 "Half a league, half a league, half a league onward, All in the Valley of Death rode the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  hundred". There's not to do and die ...". I forget the rest, now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 "There's not to reason why" Yes, I've read that one, b
ut what about the other one you mentioned, something about Lucknow? You don't remember. Do you remember how they taught you to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, we had a little book with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  letters, or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  at the least. There was ... same as 'on', }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  words, you see. That's how we begun. 'On', with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  ... a page with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 words, we had to learn those. Same as 'on' and 'no' and 'it'. Then as you got older you had the bigger, the longer words, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean it went from small to big words through the book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. I used to do a lot of reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember what the books were called, what the readers were called? Were they called 'readers' then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I think so. They were red, I remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what about learning to count and that kind of thing, do you remember how they taught you that? And learning sums?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
We had most ... blackboards. We didn't have things like the children have today. They have things ...individual things, don't they? But we didn't, it was put on the blackboard you see, and ...a slate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you copied it down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Copied it down, yes, and as you copied you learnt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And how many were there in a class, do you remember, at the Weslyan School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well I don't think there was so many in those days as there are today. I don't think there were near so many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Could you hazard a guess as to how many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And there were many more teachers, too. Well, teachers were more ... you could get teachers easier than you can today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember how many teachers there were in that school when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, there was Mr. Richardson, was the headmaster, Miss Taylor was the mistress; and Miss Bates; meek Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 Meacher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  ... oh, 5 or 6.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And about how many children, have you any idea, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I've got no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did they have a roll-call? Used they to read out a register?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
There was a register, oh, yes, yes, yes. Oh, Yes, you had to have ... they'd call your name out and you'd say, 'present, Miss'. And we had to make curtsies in those days, and the boys 
touched their hats. Oh, we had to curtsey. And on prize-giving day we had to go up to the desk and get our prize and we had to be sure and curtsey then, if not we got reprimanded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did every child get a prize?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No! But I got ... years right off ..
. several. I've got them in there, now. Oh, yes, I was at the ... my name always came out. I wasn't away very of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 and if it was ... well, she'd send me to school if I didn't feel very well, and they'd send me home, so I got me mark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was the prize for at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance, or good work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
dance. They didn't give it for good work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Nor for good conduct? Just for at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, just for at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And how many prizes were given for at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance, to a standard? Just one for the best at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, each one, each one had one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Each standard, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, each individual child, you all had one. If you made the at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 dance, whatever class you were in, you had your book. And when they had an alcohol ... they had a man come down once a year ... or once in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years, I think it was, to give a lecture on alcohol, and he'd give the ... spend most of the afternoon and you just sat, like that, and lis}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ed. When he'd gone, the next day you had a form ... he left the
 forms behind, you were to write that ... all what you knew, and they were to be posted on to him and if you did it very well you got a certificate. Well, I did mine, I got a certificate both times ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years right off. And a book. Nobody else had a book, but I had an extra one, I had a book, a lovely book. I was proud of myself that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was the book called, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 "The Crusaders", it was called, the book. But the certificates, I've got them now, I never had them framed - well, she didn't bother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she take any interest in your progress at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, no, not at all. And we did needlework. Of course, I was very good at that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 The teacher used to give me needlework ... I slept at Granny's ... to take home then, I used to sit and do it at Granny's, get it finished. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Perhaps it was putting gathers in, setting gathers. Well, I loved that, picking up every little one and ... put in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of things did you make at needlework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, we made ... like, dresses ... Y
our mothers, if they wanted them, they could send the material round and we could make it at school. I made her a couple of nightdresses, and I made some pillowcases, and ... oh, lots of things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you learnt your embroidery at school, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I didn't do that at school, no, no. I did that after left ... I couldn't do it at home, there. I learnt that after I left ... well, I used to make my aprons when I was out in service. Morning aprons and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6488516\charrsid10629010 embroidered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  ones. I used to buy the embroi
dery and make them, those little, tiny ones. I used to love doing that ... by hand. I used to get up at 5 o'clock in the morning and sit on a summer morning, up in the attic. It was lovely up there, early morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And that was in your first job, was it? I mean, not the first one, because that was at Cudmore's, the first one, wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The first job was just here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where Cudmore's used to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, well I wasn't only - I was 16 then, and I stopped a week. No, 14 then, and I stopped a week and went back to school for }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 About school again. Did any of the teachers particularly encourage you at school? I mean were they taking an interest in you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, they... no, you were one of the herd, you see. Couldn't do it, they hadn't 
the time for it. But they were kind to me, I noticed, because I used to notice loss of little things. They had lunch at school, the teachers at 11, when we went out to play they had their lunch, as well as we went out to play. And they'd get me to go to t
he shop and get some biscuits for them, and they always gave me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  because I'd got no lunch. I was never given lunch at home, to take. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  o'clock, you know, the play break. They used to give me ... and I think that's what they did it for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Because they felt sorry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. They were very kind to me, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have music at the school, at all? Singing and playing instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We had singing, just plain singing, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No playing of instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you ever wish you could learn the piano or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, It's the first thing I should have learnt and learnt to sing. Miss Went - I don't know whether you know her. Perhaps you don't - she said to me a little while back, 'oh, Kate', she said to me,
 'you'd have made well if you'd had money spent on you'. Well, I'm in the old people's choir. And the Chapel choir, for 20 years I was in that choir. I love it. I wished I'd've been trained and I wished I'd learnt to play the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You never learnt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, only if I'd had the money I should have played meself. But I never had any encouragement. I never had any push, you see, to help ... no one to help me. Still, never mind. I got through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Looking back, from what you tell me, it sounds as if you had quite a sad time in some ways, but do you think you of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  felt unhappy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I don't ... I think I did. Definitely, I must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember crying on your own, and that sort of thing, wishing life were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I was
 always crying. I was always crying. I know a person ... she told her father or her mother when she got home, she said, 'somebody's been hitting that little Katie Bailey, she's crying, her eyes are, red.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did people hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, that was the woman, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, she was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Nobody else did. They were all kind to me. They felt sorry for me, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Now, I wonder if we could go back to the time you left school. Could you tell me what year that was, that you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I was 16 then. You've got to take 16 from 77, haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You're 77, are you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So it was 61 years ago - about 1907 you must have left. And when you left school what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I went to ... to be a nursemaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 To ... at ... Opposite the village hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was the work like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I did the ... took the baby out ... little girl out and I did light duties, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I lived in, yes, and I have half a crown a week. And I stayed 5 years. That was my first place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you went straight there from school, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, no, I didn't. Oh, yes, I did, that's quite right, because I mentioned about the place before, when I went back to school for 2 years, didn't I. Well, this player I went after I'd started out again and I was ... stayed there for 5 years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So it wasn't absolutely your first job after you left school, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, after I left school properly, because, you see, you remember I said I had to go back for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years because I wasn't strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I knew that, but I just wanted to get it on to the recorder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, well this would be my real first place. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years I stayed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can we go back to your very first job because I haven't got it 
on the recording - about the very first job you had which didn't last very long because your health wasn't good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It only lasted the week. You see, the house ... there was no, what you call, modern ... it wasn't modernized in any way, you see, no wate
r laid, or anything, and they were ... assistants all lived in. It's over there, that's the house - and I couldn't do it, it was too heavy for me and I was ill on the Friday night. I'd been there just a week. And the Board arranged that I should go back t
o school, 'cos it was the Board of Guardians I was under, you see, as I came from the Home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did the Board of Guardians arrange for you to go to that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5727481\charrsid10629010  foster}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  mother was told to find me something to do and she thought being in Bentley it would be near, first place, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you go for an interview before you took the job? For the little one that only lasted a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I think the lady came over to see me. Yes, she came to see me and of course, she engaged me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How did you feel about that first job, did you want to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, I didn't mind. I wanted to go and do something. I'd left school, you see, I couldn't stay in school any longer because the age for leaving school was 14 then. It was a Board school 
then. Well then, later on it was a Council school and now it's a preparatory school, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Primary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Primary, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was the school over there by the station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes. Not when I first of all went to school, I didn't. That was Me
thodist, and I used to come over and watch that one being built. 1896 I think that was built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When did you transfer to the one over there, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When I was 6, you see, when it was built, the new one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I see, you were just there for a few years and then you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  when I was ... I went there for about 3 years, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Cos you started school at 3, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Well, I was born in 1890 and that was built in 1896, so it would give me 3, wouldn't it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years I should be, then - the 3 when I come and 3 I put into school there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So when you went to this place, what were your hours that you had to work? For the one you were just at for a week
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I think I went at 8 and I came home at 2 o'clock in the afternoo
n. I came home after lunch. And I liked it very, very much. I was very happy, that little week and I was so proud, but you see I was ... couldn't do it. You see, all the water had to be carted up and down, with assistants living in made a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What exactly was your job called, that you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I was like a day-girl, they would call you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you did general housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, there was no babies ... children there to look after. I just did light work, light duties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what work was so particularly heavy there? Was it the carrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was carrying water up and down stairs, and that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was a shop, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did they sell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Everything. Everything. Drapery, grocery, shoes, anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you meet any new people when you went there, or did you know everybody already when you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't know them, not the shop assistants. They were ... some of them were strangers, lived in. And they kept ... the post office wa
s there, too. It was the post office as well. No, I didn't know them. I'd seen the lady about. She was a Miss Sands, from Colchester. Sweet, wonderfully sweet woman, very sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So you got along there quite well with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, there was a ... 3 grown up children, of course, not babies. There was 1 daughter and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  boys, one was blind, nearly, and the other was a cripple.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you were only 14?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I was only 14, that's right, yes. And I stayed a week. And then Mother took me down
 to the Relieving Officer, they called him, he came round with the money each week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  shillings a week, she had for me. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 And he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  used to bring the money round, and of course she ... and he lived down the bottom end of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 reen, in that long white house where people named King live in. It stretched right back ... if you stand on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 reen here and look down the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
reen, that house stands right plain. And she took me down there and asked him about it. He said, 'well, what I should do if I were you, keep her at h
ome'. He said, 'you can't send her like that any more', he said, 'but I'll put it before the Board Meeting on Wednesday', that was Board day. And it went before the meeting and they granted me 2 years at school, again. Well, they really knew, I think, som
e
 of them - I don't know whether Master was there, Mr. Burden, or whether that was his daughter. Anyway, I think they must have know, by granting me that, I was delicate when I was in there, you see. 'Cos really in the first place I shouldn't have gone the
re like that. If I'd've gone where I went for the 5 years, taking the children. 'Course, I was always fond of children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you went back to the school, what standard had you passed when you left that first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 X.7, yes, and I stayed the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In X.7 again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, yes, I couldn't do anything else, you see there were no schools to get ... well, Miss Went - we were talking about Miss Went - she said, 'if money be spend on you, Kate, you would've made good'. But, you see...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But you just had to repeat the same work, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, there weren't the facilities that there are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you went back for those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years, do you think you learnt anything new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't learn any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Nobody took the trouble to try and give you anything extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, they weren't interested. No, I just carried on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you do any work during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, I had to do sums and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Sorry, I mean any work earning money. Did you have odd jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Because you told me last time that your foster father forbade you to do the shopping any more, for people, didn't he, because it was too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Ah, yes, but that was before I went to school. I was a little, wee mite to do that. That was after I come out of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So when you went back to school for those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years you didn't have any means of earning money then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Not even errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't have any money at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have any friends in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, you see, I'd got a stigma. I came from the Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there other children from the Union in Gt. Bentley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, there was ... another girl came out with myself. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  girls - a girl Roper, a girl Hobson and a girl Cook and they were in homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the village, yes. They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you mix with them at all? Did they go to the same school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we all had to go to the same school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you mix with them, were they friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, 
we were always friendly, just us, but we always stood apart. They didn't ... 'I'm not playing with you, you come out of the Union'. I had that said to me many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And then, after those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years you got this job as a nursemaid ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But these ot
her girls were older than myself, so I didn't know much about them after they left. I know one went to Miss Went's grandmother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you went to the job as a nursemaid, can you tell me something about your duties there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I had to help
 dress the little girl in the mornings and play with her, do what she wanted to do; and take her ... we used to go errands, do the errands. And then in the afternoon she was put in the pram and I had to take her out for an hour or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , so I used to go a long, long, long walk, But I must not associate with anyone. They were very funny, those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there other nursemaids pushing their babies around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Different people there were, yes, but I mustn't stop and speak. I know I met my foster father on
e day and he spoke. And he said I just said, 'hello and he \{ILLEGIBLE\} when I got on, I always remember that. He said, 'what have I done you should}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 \rquote n\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  speak to me ...', he said, 'you mustn't be afraid of that woman like that,' he said, 'that won't do'. Bu
t she was very much like that. It wouldn't have done for me to stop to talk, somebody would've told her and I ... I was afraid of her, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was she a good employer in some ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, she wanted to go out of you all she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She worked you hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Very hard. Oh, it was a hard place. As I got older ... well, you see, I was there 5 years. Well, I went back again there after a few years and that was hard, very hard then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was harder when you went back, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. You see, I was older. I was ill then and I had to leave, and there were no ... I got ulcers and I was anaemic, you see, and Dr.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010  Athill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 was the doctor then and he said it was the anaemia brought the ulcers on and he said I must have a rest. She didn't like that
 at all, but I had to go home for nearly 6 months. And there were no ... I'd had all my front teeth out which were very, very sound although there was pyorrhea in them. They were tight in and I had to have every one out. I was only 16 - between 16 and 17 
then. I had to have them all out and there was no insurance, and I was getting half a crown a week and I had to pay the foster parent for doing my washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was she not collecting any money for you any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, when I first went out it stopped. Oh, she wasn't keeping me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you went home for 6 months, did you go back to her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I had to go, for I had nowhere to go, but she was not nice with me at all. It was horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think she resented having to keep you then, when you were not earning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
I think so, yes. And then I had all me teeth out. Well, I'd got no money to pay for them, so she paid. They were 12 guineas. I always remember that. And she paid it, and I had to pay her back when I went back. I didn't have any
 new clothes, only for what I wanted to wear in the house, the uniform. We had to wear uniform those days. A print dress and a white apron and cap. Then in the afternoon it was a black dress, little starched apron and cap.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have to pay for your uniform yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes! Some people got it ... the people they worked for paid for it, but I never got in a job like that. Never. I always had to buy my own uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How long did it take you to pay back your foster mother for ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I can't tell you, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Quite a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Must have done. Must have done. But I paid her. And if I went for a holiday I had to pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In that job, were there any other children, or just the little girl you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well ther
e was another boy ... a boy, older, Stanley. I think ... I don't know how old he was ... older than his sister. His sister was the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you not have to look after him at all, or do anything for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I had to look after him, but ... I used t
o take the both out. But latterly he got so I think he went to school. But he had an accident. They kept ... they were a farm, they kept cows, 'cos they lived ... moved from the shop I just told you, in front of Mr. Simmonds's shop near the garage, they w
e
nt to that house over the station, the first house, Plough Farm. They went to that house over the station, the first house, Plough Farm. They went and lived there. They had a farm there, and a cow kicked him, and it kicked him ... he was hit, I think it w
as, so he'd got one leg longer than the other. Well, I used to have to wheel him out in a big perambulator and that was bigger than me. I was such a tiny, little thing, and I used to take him - oh, ever such a way round, and he had a w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  on his foot, you see, to pull that leg longer. So I had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  to look after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have to do any cooking for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't do the cooking - oh, they kept }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  maids, and she did the cooking herself, the mistress of the home - house - and the other maid did the
 bedrooms and things like that. I did the light jobs; set the tea; washed up, you see. And she kept a dairy, well I used to do the dairy things, scull them all out when I wasn't looking after the children, in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have any time off during the day that was just your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, not in the day, we never did. We had one evening a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of time would that evening be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 From }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 'till }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , or 7 'till 9, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And if you'd come back later than 9, would something have been said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I should think so! I should think so! They always said at home, my foster parents, I was always frigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 tene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 d of being in late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you have a half day or full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Day once a month. That was to go shopping. And I sometime
s, if I saved enough after the teeth business was all over, I used to go to Colchester with the foster mother. If I wanted a new hat or anything like that, she'd come with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And on that day did you have any duties at all in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we didn't get off 'till about 10 o'clock. Had to do so much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you still had to be back at 9, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes, still be back at 9, never no later. But Sunday, I think we had Sunday morning ... one Sunday night off once a fortnight. Y
ou see, we changed over. The other maid would have it ... one Sunday night off and I'd have the next Sunday night, because there was the children ... Sunday nights, I used to sit after they'd gone to bed and lis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , see if they cried or anything and I could go to the bookcase and get a book to read if I liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You liked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, I used to ... oh, yes, I used to like that. The Girls' Own, her daughter ... she had a daughter died before this other daughter was born. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 Her name was Greta, she was abo
ut 14, and there used to be her books, and she had them all bound, Little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 Dorrit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010  and all things like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So I used to go and she used to let me do that. I thought it was an honour, and I used to sit and write poetry out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Copy it out, or make up your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I have made it up lately, but I used to copy it out then. I was always fond of poetry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you get on well with the other maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, I got on well with ... she had several .. She was always changing. They wouldn't stay. Peop
le wouldn't stay, it was too hard. But I had to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Because you were from the Union, you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I mean, foster parent - no, the Union didn't ... they'd finished with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I see, they didn't take any more interest in you after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, they took an interest because ... I'll tell you why, but I've never heard of any ... never heard of them doing it for anyone else. At Christmas they sent me a \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 scarf}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  at Christmas, pale blue. I should think that was ... that with big bal
ls at the end, and didn't I put that on and think I was ... Then another time they sent me a form with a penny stamp put on. That was to encourage me to save my pennies 'till I'd got 12, and then have a book and save money, you see, Post Office. I thought
 that was kind of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, very kind. Do you think it was that daughter of the master that sent you the scarf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I don't know because they changed hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, so it wasn't the same people when you got the scarf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well I don't think
 it could have been 'cos ... But it was Mr. Lockey first and his wife died and then his daughter kept house for him. Well then a Mr. Barnard - I think it was Barnard, some such a name as that, and his wife took it over ... Burden. Mr. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12204074 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  Mrs. Burden, they took it over. But I think it must have been the Lockey family, because she used to invite me in - as I said before, little pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ty pieces. She must have taken an interest in me, you see. And it just have been then, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That you got the blue scarf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You must have been very thrilled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I was thrilled. I can see myself ... only for Sundays I wore it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can I ask you a bit more about your job? So you were saying, you got up at 6 o'clock in the morning in that nursemaid's job, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can you try and remember what a day was like? You had to get up at 6 and what was the first thing you'd do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Clean about 20 pairs of boots out in the shed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The cow people's boots; who kept the cows. Was that the labourers' boots? Who did all the boots belong to that you cleaned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well the sons. She'd got grown-up sons, you see, and they were butchers as well, and I had all those boots to clean. The sons ... you see, they were courting, so they had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  pairs, their working boots and their evenings'. One boy was at college and there were 3 at home ... 4 at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was including Stanley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I didn't count the little children's boots, the little girl's and boy's. I did those, but I'd got all those to do before breakfast.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was that blacking they used to use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, a penny a cake. Yes, and you put vinegar with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It was difficult to work, I believe, difficult to get them to look ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, you couldn't specially butchers, there was blood and all on them, I used to have to clean them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So it was all the family's boots you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The family's boots to clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And anybody else's in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 If anybody was staying there they had to be done. And there was her boots to clean. She had hers done as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 After you'd done the boots, what was the next thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, as I said, she had a dairy. I had a cup of tea and I had to take the milk out, in cans, round the village green. Cold weather, frosty, snow, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 I h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ad to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean delivering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Not in a big hand cart, or anything, they were the milk cans. Used to cut my poor little fingers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With a piece of wire tied between them, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And then when you got to people's houses ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Butter, fresh butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You took that round too, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How did you carry the butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I made a special journey with the butter. That was done up in little pats, quarter lbs. and half lbs.. The quarter lbs. were round p
ats and the half lbs. were the square pats.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And would you take that round at another time of the day, or also early morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, perhaps after ... after I'd done the milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How many houses would you call at with the mild, roughly speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would it be more than half a dozen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, more than that, a couple of dozen, I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you got there, how did you measure out the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, it was measured, my dear, in cans. That was ordered
. That was ordered, you see, and there's a quart and a pint in that one. Well, I knew the cans, you see. The can held just a quart and the pint held a pint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But that must have meant that you had to keep going backwards and forwards to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, dear, how terrible!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 
And there was one old lady - well, she was sister to the master, Mr. Wright ... his sister, I called on her, 'cos his mother ... she looked after the mother, and she always said, 'come in dear, drink that
 cup of tea quickly and eat the biscuit and don't say I give it to you'. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Every morning I had that cup of tea and a biscuit. That was Auntie Sadie. Her real name was Sarah, but they called her Sadie. She was a dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And it must have helped you on your job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, it warmed me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How long would it take you to do those milk deliveries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I should say an hour. When I came back I had me breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That would be the first thing you'd have to eat, would it, except for Auntie Sadie's biscuit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Who did you eat your breakfast with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With the other maid, just us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the kitchen, would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, in the dining room when they'd all finished. We took the chairs, sat down in the chairs that they had, you see, in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what would you have for your breakfast to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, anything going. Perhaps some cold sausages, pork cheese or anything like that. She wasn't ... she didn't fuss us up, I can tell you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have anything like porridge, or cereal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And tea? More tea to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Fresh tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't know whether it was fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you have bread and butter and honey, perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Bread and dripping. We never had much butter, only for tea. We had dripping from the beef, you see, what she cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was it good dripping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, it was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you'd had your breakfast, what was the next thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Empty the slops, you see, in the bedrooms. What I had to do, and they had to all be brought down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In pails?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  bedrooms, and all used, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  beds in some. And then I'd empty the slops .. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Where would you empty the slops, would that be outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, bring them downstairs and cart them right down to the toilet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Which was outside, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you clear the breakfast away and wash up, or did the other maid do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The other maid cleared ... she wouldn't have us work together. She would not. D
idn't like talk, you see, and waste a minute. She used to do that, and I used to go up with her and help her make the beds every morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You were allowed to do that together? That was allowed, was it, for you to make the beds with help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She always wanted me to make the beds with her, always, the mistress did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, the mistress. You made the beds with the mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, she always had me upstairs to make the beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she talk to you and make conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, she always talked to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In a friendly way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, oh, yes, in a friendly way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you made the beds ... about how many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 There was ... Bertha's bed was in with her Mummy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12204074 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010  Daddy's. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She'd got a little cot in there, a small cot; and Stan
ley was in with his brother Wilfred, Wilfred and Frank; and then there was Tom and Arthur, they had another bed. They were in what we call the skylight room. Then there was our beds, our bedroom, and we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  maids slept together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I'd never been used to sleeping with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you find that difficult to get used to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And after you'd made the beds what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Went to the shop if there was anything to get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was Bertha doing all the while you were making the beds and having your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She was playing with the toys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have to keep an eye on her while you were doing these other duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, sometimes I'd take her up with me, but her mother general
ly give her something to do and I'd go up and make the beds, and then I should have to look after ... take her out and play with her, and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do errands, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, take her to do the errands.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How old was she when you first took your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I should think she was about 3. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  or 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were you supposed to teach her manners, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Her mother did all that, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, she did all that. It wouldn't do to dictate to her child, she wouldn
't let you. She wouldn't think you were good enough, not even if you come from a better home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was the little girl well behaved on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, she wasn't bad, but \{BLANK\} the little boy, he was a dear. I've got a letter at home he wrote me. We
 had a day, as I said, once a month, and I went home one Monday and the foster lady - the foster mother I lived with - she'd got a baby, she went 17 years in between one to the other. And I went home to take him out. And he wrote me a letter. And I loved 
that child. I've still got his letter - 'you are the best serving maid I ever had'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was the foster mother's little boy who said that, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, her son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We were on to when you took the little girl out, so the rest of the morning were you with the child, with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid863914\charrsid10629010  Bertha?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Or perhaps she'd go in with her mother, perhaps, and I'd have the potatoes to do. Vegetables, you see, for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time would you have your own dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  o'clock, after they'd all finished. We 
cleared the table and then we sat down to lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 At the same table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And the same food did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, yes, we had the same as they did. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would you have a hot dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we had hot dinners every day. Yes, and they'd got their own meat, you see, their own butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you eat well there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
We lived well, yes, but of course, I got wrong. I never eat fat. Couldn't eat it, and she used to be so cross with me. But I couldn't eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean she would expect you to eat the fat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. She said I was wasteful, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So she even noticed what you had on your plate, do you mean? She would supervise you to the ex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 t of seeing what you ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, you see, she cut i
t off for us ... she'd cut our dinners off and we came in and sat down to eat them and she'd notice it. Sit there, perhaps and darn socks while we were there. You couldn't be alone and talk. Never left you alone, you know. You mustn't talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How strange. Even when you were eating you weren't allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, you was afraid to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Because she was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You felt afraid and didn't feel free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we had puddings. We lived well there only as I say, I couldn't eat the fat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of puddings did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, she made milk puddings - mostly milk puddings, with plenty of milk, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean a custard, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, custard and fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Stewed fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 After the dinner did the maid clear away then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Used to clear away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You'd help the maid, then, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I used to help clear away and perhaps sometimes I'd help wipe up. But I'd got to go and dress after that, put my black d
ress on and take Bertha out for the afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you told me you took and hour or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  over that, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I kept her out 'till teatime, and took her in to teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time was teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 About 5 o'clock, that was 4 to 5. Then I 
would stop with her while she had her tea, 'cos perhaps her mother was writing letters, or something, or doing some of the business work, and I would stay with her, tell her tales and read to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The other maid would get the tea, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, she'd be getting their tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And would she get Bertha's tea, also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, she'd ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You didn't have much to do with the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well I don't know, I would cut the bread and butter and then I'd give Bertha some. You see, I would cut 
the bread and butter for tea sometimes, you see. Well then, I'd give Bertha hers ... her tea, and then when she'd had her tea, I used to take her out and play with her a little longer, and then Mrs. Wright would have her while I had my tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would she still sometimes be in the same room with you while you had your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Mrs. Wright would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, oh, yes, she wouldn't leave us alone. Oh, no, we were never left alone. And then after then ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did you have for your tea then? Bread and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Jam if we wanted, and then ... they used to make cakes, they had a pastry shop as well. We used to have some of the cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And tea to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you ever have meat for tea? Anything in the way of meat, at all, or cheese for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, we had dripping if we wanted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And then after tea what was the next thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well then, after tea, if it was winter time, well then of course I played with her 'till it was bed time. Mrs. Wright used to
 wash her. Her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  washed her every night and got her ready for bed and did her hair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I suppose she had long hair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, long hair, yes. She used to do her hair. She had nice hair, and she used to get her ready for bed and put her to bed. I did
n't. Of course, she kept in her mum's room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she always put her to bed, or did you sometimes do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, she never left, always put her to bed herself. If it was late she put her to bed herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Why do you think she always put her to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't know why. I of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 wondered. Because, you see, she'd had one girl which she lost and she never ... she couldn't forget it, and I think she took so much ... she loved this one so much, you see. It was different to when I lived over there at th
e other place. I used to put the little girl to bed there and did everything for her, nearly. She wouldn't let anyone else, she used to say, 'I want Kate, Mamma', she'd say, 'all right dear, you shall have her'. She came and saw me Saturday. She lives in 
Frinton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Is she the one who ....? Did you have any holidays besides your regular time off, your own day off that you told me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I did, but I couldn't ... I'd got nowhere to go. My foster mother didn't want me, so I didn't have the holidays I could have had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What holidays could you have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I could have had a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, but I didn't you see, I'd got nowhere to go. Even after I got over to this place and I wanted ... they were going to Ipswich to see th
e lady's mother, they would take ... this Miss Newman, the daughter, Gwyneth, with them and I could have time off, but my mistress used to pay for me to go out to sleep because my foster mother wouldn't have me, she said she hadn't got room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Had she got room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, she could have 4 soldiers planted on her during the War. It was money all the time. But then they would have paid, they did pay. They paid the neighbour to have me. They were pleased to have me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Can you remember on Christmas }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ay when you were with the Wrights, did you stay there for the day with them? Or did you go to the foster mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I went to the foster mother's part of the day, yes, after dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What was Christmas }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ay like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I can't remember. I don't think it was worth remembering, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 There weren't presents, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I never had many presents, only one mother, where I worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They gave you presents there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Why did you go on to the Newman's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, it was getting ... what was it? I'd been away for a month or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , ill, and when I went back ... she was a woman that didn't like you being ill, you know. You mustn't be ill. She didn't want you ... and when I went back ... I'd been away }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  months, or 3 with thi
s anaemia and ulcers, gastric ulcers, and the morning I went back I was doing up the stove, and she said, Oh, Kate, I've come to the conclusion that I think it would be better if you left. You're not strong enough for our job. You're not strong enough for
 the work'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Just like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Just like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she say she was sorry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No. That upset me, rather, and I told the foster mother about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Was she understand, sympathetic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She said, 'it's rather strange, 'cos you couldn't help being ill', I said, 'no, I couldn't.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid863914\charrsid10629010 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  Anyway, I thought to meself, 'well, I'll have to look for another place'. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 
This place opened out here, and I went home on the Wednesday evening, my night out 'till 9, and I told the foster mother about it so she said, 
'well, I should ask her if you can go over and see Mr. Poulton, as the same people that I went with for the week, they were still there, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
So I said, 'yes, I think I will. She said, 'I should'. So when I got back, the next morning I said, 'would you
 mind if I had a little time off Friday afternoon? I've made an appointment'. She said, 'what for?' I said, 'well I don't know if I'll get it or not, I've put in for another job'. 'Well, 'she said, 'I don't suppose I can stop you.' So I went and the next 
m
orning, while I'm making the beds with her, like I always did, she cried. She says, 'Oh, Katie, don't go. I'm awfully sorry', she said, 'I've always liked you, 'she said, 'don't go'. I said, 'I'm afraid I must, I've got another job.' She said, 'What??' I 
s
aid, 'I've got a job,' I said, 'and I can go directly I leave here,' She says, 'where?'. I said, 'over at Mr. Poulton's'. 'Oh,' she say, 'that's jumping right out of the frying pan into the fire'. I said, 'well, Father says there isn't the grease there is
 here'. I had to make pork cheese, at 10, 12 o'clock at night, for the butchers, and the lard. Help her do it. And they were big boilers, that width, no more, and she used to ... she said to me one evening, 'come along }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 Kate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , get hold of this boiler and help
 me off with it,' and we'd got to lift it on to the table. 'Oh,' I said, 'I'm sorry, but I can't'. She said, 'lift it!'. I said, 'I can't, I'm sorry'. Her husband stood there, he said, 'well, let me lift it for her', and he did lift it for me. I couldn't 
lift it! And we were there picking the bones out and making the pork cheese and more of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 ten }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 than not it was 11 and 12 at night.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I was going to ask you, because we'd got as far as putting the little girl to bed. While she was putting the little gir
l to bed what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Clearing up the toys, and that. Tidying up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, if there wasn't this pork cheese, and that, to do ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 There of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 was, was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Only once a week. She'd got some rugs, sacking, you'd 
old coats and that, you'd cut up and you used to put the thrums through ... those old fashioned, heavy ... well, I sat and did some of those in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 For her, was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I had to. Or do mending. She always mended the socks, but she wa
s ... little jobs she'd give me to do, and I was good at the needle as she thought, I suppose. Or perhaps there'd be fruit to pick over. Perhaps, I had to go out the garden pick the blackcurrants, things like that. According to the year, according to the 
job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time would that go on to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 'Till 9, have supper at 9. Then I'd got to set supper. Perhaps the other girl was out for her night out, when she wasn't, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did they eat for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Bread and cheese. They had meat and stuff like that, we didn't. We had piece of bread and cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did you drink at supper time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And then after 9 o'clock, were you off, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, we didn't go to bed 'till 10 or 11.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You still had other duties, do you mean, after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, I used to sit up in bed to put the buttons on my dresses, or aprons, or do me mending. I used to wait 'till she'd gone to bed - 'cos we had candles those days - and I used to way 'till all their lights were out, I should look out my bedroom door...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You were telling me how you got this new job at Poultons, this new job. How much longer did you work at the Wrights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I filled that ... I had to give a month's notice. Well, she gave me a month's notice, she did, she gave me 
a month's notice, you see, so I took it. She said, 'I'm sorry, Kate', she said, 'don't go'. I said, 'I'm already going, I've got a job'. She says, 'What?', I said, I've got a job,'. 'Oh,' she says, 'where?' and I told her, "Mr. Poulton's', she says, 'well
 you're jumping out of the frying pan into the fire'. 'Well,' I says, 'Father says there won't be the grease there that there is here'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did your father think about the work that you were doing, your foster father? Did he worry about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Wel
l, he couldn't have any say in it, she was boss, you see. Lots of people in the village said I never ought to have been there, it was too heavy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you were working for her did she ever praise you and tell you she thought you worked hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, sometimes she'd say, 'oh that looks very nice, Kate,' or so-and-so, now and again when she thought, but otherwise ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when you left did she give you anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, oh, no. And I came straight over here and I was here }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  months with the same people ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That you'd been at before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, the lady. Only she was dead, he'd got another wife, the man. And I was there 3 months and he committed suicide. And Newman's took over the ... they came in the May, and had the business, and I was the
re, oh, for over 40 years, and I was very happy. They were very nice people. I had everything that they had, I had my meals with them, and the little girl - well, she was little then, she was a year old. And I remember coming home and I said to my foster 
.
.. well I was telling my foster mother and father about it, but I said, 'oh, she's a dear little baby,' and he said, 'she would be, that's just up your street, now. You'll be happy now,' he says, 'you've got a baby there'. I said, 'but the lady looks ill'
.
 She did, she was white. I said, 'I hope she isn't going to be ill'. She did, she was white. I said, 'I hope she isn't going to be ill'. Dad says, 'don't you worry about that, she'll be all right'. You see, she'd been used to Ipswich, living in Ipswich an
d Harwich and they're not ... not like the country.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What wages were you getting when you left the Wright's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you were 23, I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And so you'd been with them about 7 years altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You see, I went back, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You went back after your illness
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Now in your new job, what were your duties there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, well, I had to get up and make a cup of tea first thing in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  o'clock, was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, not 'till 7. Take the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  of them in the bedroom, and take the little girl one, 'cos she had her own little bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She had a cup of tea, did she, at 1 year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, she wouldn't be that, would it. Where am I now, just wait a minute. No, she was 
a year old. She's 56 now. She was a year old when she come and she's 56 now, she told me so the other day. I said, 'I'd forgot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , dear, I thought you were 55'. She said, 'no, I'm 56, Catherine' She always called me Catherine, won't call me Kate. So did Mrs. Newman. They were very, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What did you call them? Did you call them Mrs. Newman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, or I used to give her a 'madam' sometimes and she used to laugh \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 And they used to take me out in the car with them. I was with her when she passed away and I looked after him 'till he went, after she'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So you were really treated there as one of the family, in a way that you weren't at the other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, one of the family, yes. And I used to go in the evenings to sit with
 them. In the evenings and do the needlework. I used to make and mend and we used to all be happy together. So different to the other place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were they country people? I mean, had they lived in the country for a long time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Mr. Newman, he was bor
n here in the vicarage, where the vicarage is, only it wasn't such a big place then. His father had it built. There were 5 bedrooms because there were 12 in family. They were related.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, really, did they get along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They were first cousins, my Mr. Newman and Wrights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And were they friendly cousins? I mean did they mix a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, they used to ... they'd speak, but they never visited houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you see her around when you were in the village and that sort of thing? Your old employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She didn't come out much, but she'd always speak to me. Oh, she was always very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, after all, she'd told you to go, hadn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, oh, yes. I shouldn't have gone, I don't suppose, but it was a blessing in disguise. I was better off there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The work was lighter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, she had a charwoman in, to do the heavy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you have to empty slops there, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, but he soon had everything done properly, modernized, and that. Came from a lovely home in Ipswich, he did
n't put up with that. And the little girl, I ... Sunday mornings they went to Chapel - they were big workers in the Chapel, he was organist - and I used to take the little girl out. I used to do the vegetables, and I used to take the little girl out. I us
ed to do the vegetables, and then Sunday we did no work. We kept Sunday as Sunday and always had a cold lunch. So I used to put the vegetables on and then she used to say, 'you can come and meet }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  out of Chapel, Catherine will bring you'. So I said, 'Ca
n I put such and such a frock on her?' 'Yes, if you like you know you can'. And I used to dress her up. She had some gorgeous dresses, and long curls, you know. She was a pretty little thing, dainty. She was a wee little thing, she was, but she's huge now
.
 And we used to go to church and meet them out of church - Chapel, if you like to call it that. And there was an old gentleman named Oxborough and he ... 'course, I knew him for years as a little girl ... and he'd be coming out of Chapel, he'd make straig
ht a beeline for us. She was in her pram all decorated. Every Saturday night my last job was to thread the pillowcase with the ribbon and get that all ready, put it on, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 ut strings on Saturday night on her clean bonnet and get ready for Sunday. And I can se
e her now in her pram, she looked just so. A clean cover on, a white cover, you know, with the embroidered lace, and that, on. Every Saturday night she had a clean one on, ready for Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 
And we'd go to Chapel and meet Daddy and Mummy out of Chapel, and this old gentleman come up and give us a peppermint. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
