 was there, the little girl, and she said, 'Kate does the flues' I of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  think of her like she was ... she was a sweet c
hild. And when we had company in I'd put her to bed, I'd give her \{BLANK\}
 and put her to bed and I say, 'now you go to sleep, dear,' 'Catherine, Catherine,' 'What do you want, dear?' 'Who's that downstairs?' 'Oh, well, you go to sleep, dear, I should' 'Wel
l, who is it? Tell me' Perhaps it was Uncle Len came in, or somebody. 'Can I come down?' 'Oh, no, dear, I shouldn't come down. Wait a minute'. I'd go up, perhaps and take her something and she'd go to sleep.
