es. So I said to her 'she said she'd like the little girl Jenkins, the Reverend Jenkins, little girl to come in a little while with her'. She said, 'Well, Margery can come in if you like. You run along Catherine and ask her, will you?' I said, 'Yes, I wil
l ask her'. She said, 'I would like her to come in a little while, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3414131\charrsid10629010 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
, and play', so Margery came in. Well, I said to Margery about half pas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 7, I said, 'you've had a half hour over, dear, now it's time to go to bed now'. I said, 'Margery, it's time for 
you to go, dear' so she said, 'all right'. So she said, 'must Margery go?' I said, 'oh, yes, dear, she must go, she's got to go to bed'. 'Oh, all right'. I said, 'look, she can stop and have some supper with you, then she'll go.' 'Oh, that would be lovely
'. So I cut them some Bovril sandwiches. We called it 'B. and B', because it was dripping with Bovril spread over. She loved it. Dripping out of the joint. So I gave it ... Margery had to have hers quickly.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
