h
ty. Where did you get that book from?' She said, 'Off the shelf'. 'Well,' I said, 'that's naughty. Now get your supper like a good girl.' I said, 'If you don't I shall eat it'. So she sat there ... I crept in a little while after, she sat there reading an
d
 I took her sandwiches and I ate them. I didn't want them but I did eat them. She cried, oh she did cry. I said, 'you didn't think I'd do it, did you, dear?' She said, I didn't' I said, 'Now, perhaps you'll eat your supper another time. Come on, your mumm
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  and dadd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
