\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time did she go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, she went to bed about half past 6 to 7, and she could have a book for a little while, and then she'd go off.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there any other children in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 No, only her, and I remember ... and she never had a sweet given her from home, 'co
s Mummy used to ... although they kept a shop she was never allowed to have money to spend for sweets, or eat a lot of sweets, but she'd give her one now and again, and it was always, 'give Catherine one, Mummy'. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I always had to have one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she spend more time with you than with her mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, no I don't think so. We were both ... we worked together, her mother and I, you see. We worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you have to take her for a long walk in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I took her out in her pram in the afternoon. She was washed and dressed, another little frock on. Every time everyday it was a fresh frock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you do washing and ironing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I used to help ... but a lot of it went out, but the babies things, her little cloth
es were always done at home. I should do them, and do them all frilled like that, with lace. You know, they'd got lace on them. They were the little silk dresses those days and poke bonnets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there other maids in that household, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, the
re was only myself, too. But you see, he had a charwoman in and I think that's better any day. I think one maid is quite enough and you get on better, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What time off did you have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I had the ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  evenings a week there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Until the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 with Sunday. I stayed in sometimes on a Sunday, but very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you went out on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Sunday night, and went out in the morning, and went out in the afternoon - back at half past 4, got tea, then went to a plac
e of worship. Then got in at 9.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And the other evenings? What sort of time were you off then? The other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  evenings in the week, what hours were you off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I was with them about, from 6 'till 9.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What would you do on your evenings off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I used to go home. And then I got friendly with another woman, just opposite here and I used to go there with her and sit with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you also have a day off for shopping, like you had at your other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I could have any time if I
 asked. I could get time off. And if there was anything on they'd pay my ... buy me a concert ticket or anything like that, you see. Oh, yes, they were very nice. She was a sweet woman, very sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And if you were worried about things and had problems on your mind, could you tell her about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I could open out to her, you see, yes. That made all the difference to me. She took my part in every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would it be right to say that she was the first woman you had been able to talk to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Oh, yes, it was. Yes, it was. She was a sweet woman and she must have liked me, else she wouldn't've ... if she went out anywhere she always brought me something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What wages did you get there when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I don't think I ... my wages weren't very high, I must say that. I think they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  shillings still. And I know, during the War, all I had was 10/- a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 During which war was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 1914 to 1918, the First World War. But I didn't mind that, 'cos she made it up in o
ther ways, and you can't have it every way. And it was a happy home. I wasn't made to feel I was an outcast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she give you any clothes ever? Did you have any extras in that sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, I didn't have any extra clothes in any way. No I did
n't. But I used to make my own aprons, you see, that helped me, and she let me use her machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she teach you how to use the machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She'd help me in any way like ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Like a mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 More than the foster mother had been?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, oh, yes, mo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 e than the foster mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did the foster mother meet her and get along with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They didn't sort of get into contact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did they entertain much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, they had ... yes, they used to entertain a good bit, and they did it properly, too. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In those years before the First War, and during the War, what sort of entertaining did they do at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, during the War they had the soldiers in, a lot in, you see. They used to entertain the officers, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the evening, would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. We had one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 billeted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  there, officers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what sort of entertainment would they give them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, a singing evening, or ...'cos he was a lovely baritone voice, 
he'd got. And the daughter, she sings like a bird, and she can play any piece of music put in front of her. 'Course, she went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  colleges. And then they paid, then, didn't they? They paid for colleges in those days. Today they get a grant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And she learnt music at the college, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, but she learnt - Miss Went first taught her, and she'd got such little, tiny hands that Miss Went said she'd never play 'cos she hadn't got the octaves. But she did in time, she persevered. Her little feet .. she only takes a one shoe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you take an interest in her school work when she started going to school
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Well, she went to this school 'till she was 11, and then she went to Colchester, so we didn't have much, really, to do with her that way. Yo
u see, she had tip top teachers there. And from there she went to Bedford College, and she went to another college - she went to Upminster, there too. She's a Froebel mistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I was wondering if you can remember anything in any way that life in the v
illage changed during the 1914-1918 war. Do you remember if it made any difference to your life, for example, that there was a war on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I think it was harder, you see, because during those years we were all worried about the fighting, and that, 
weren't we. And we had soldiers in. It made a lot of work, you know. We had a soldiers and his wife billeted there, and that was a business house. But as I say, she did the cooking and she was a good mistress, very good. She did what she could and she did
 
more than some. We were very happy. But I don't think the ... having the soldiers helped at all. It made extra work, and not only that, some of them weren't very nice. They weren't all gentlemen. But we had some very nice officers there, very nice. And th
en there was the fire watching, but that would come in ... I think that came in the next war, the 1939 to 1945, there was the Home Guard and all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you remember rationing at all in the First War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, I remember rationing. It was terri
ble. We didn't have, only so much bread, did we? And so much milk. And sugar, well, we couldn't even get sugar half the time, did we? We didn't get sugar. But of course, living in the shop I don't know much about it. We had plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mentioned last 
time that at school you used to have to curtsey and I wondered if, in the village, when you met someone, a lady or someone, were you expected to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Only in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That's all, only in school, or ... when we took our prizes, and t
hat, you see. There was a board of ... what do they call those men? They were not on the council; they were not magistrates. What are they? If they came in we had to, you see. And I think it was your left foot ... no. \{BLANK\}
 the right one up, don't you, you see, and the boys touched their hats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
In the village when you were a child and a young woman, what were they ... were there certain people who were very important in the village? You know, whom people looked up to at that time? I don't mean actuall
y the names of the people, but I mean in certain positions, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, I mean, there was the ... the vicars, you would, wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. But were there certain families living in big houses, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You didn't get many big families round here, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean everybody was more of less the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 More of less on the level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And was it the same at the school? Were most of the children more or less the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, you see, they didn't go to Colchester School '
till they were 11, so they all came here. But we were all about the same, there was not much distinction.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
And you weren't made to feel that some people were much better off ... the children didn't feel that some were much better off and some worse off than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .., perhaps they had the feeling, but they weren't...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 They weren't treated differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Do you think when you started work and when you got your job, you know, at the Wrights and then later on at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Newman's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , did it make any difference to your outlook on life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, I was so much happier. Much more happier and I didn't seem tied down and I wasn't afraid. I lost that fear. I seemed under the other woman. This one tried to get me out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You mean Mrs. Newman did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. Well, she was a sweet woman. She really was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And you were a happier person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, ever so happy there. And happy ... do anything... she'd do anything for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 more questions, because we are very interested in the kind of different way that people had their meals, and things, at that time. When you were at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Newman's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  can you tell me something about how the table was laid and who carved the joint, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, he always carved the joint. Mr. Newman always carved the joint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did he always sit in the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, regularly had the same place at the table. And of course, she was at the head of the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Gwenyth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 eat with you when she got a little bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, she always had to have her little high chair brought in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She didn't have her meals at a separate time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I used to feed her before, but we let her sit at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I see, she sat with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She had a book in her little chair. You see, that was a chair that was ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 
3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  positions. You could put it that way ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You could either put it right up, or it's a little low one on the ground, with a tray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, and then you could put it at the table, so she could ... 
her little table was fixed, and she'd sit and look at the pictures. A good little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 should}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And when she served up the meal, would she put it in dishes on the table, like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, we served them up ... dished them up in the kitchen and took them on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did she help you? Did she help the food on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, she always did all the helping, you see. And I never went short of anything. I was treated as one of her own, and if I wanted any more I wasn't afraid to ask for 
it. But I never did, because I'm not a big eater. I'd got the feeling I could come again, you see. I felt free. That was it. The shop was like this, the kitchen was like this and that door, you go straight through into the shop which they never locked it 
a
way from me. They never did. I could walk in there as easy as I could walk in my kitchen. And sometimes I used to say, 'oh, Mrs., I should like a peppermint', she'd say, 'would you care for one. I'll get you one out the shop', you see, and she'd get me ha
lf a dozen. I wouldn't dream of going in. I wouldn't. Wouldn't dream. No, I'd rather ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And she always gave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 You never served in the shop at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would you have liked to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I think I should have done, but I was quite happy where I was. Quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And in the evening did you have a tea, like you had at the Wrights? The same kind of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, we had eggs sometimes. And sometimes I'd put egg and haddock. You know what I mean, fresh ... smoked fillet
, put an egg on top. She'd say, 'do one for yourself, Catherine'. Oh, yes, I was treated the same. And if it was strawberry time and he went out and bought some I always had a little dish of strawberries. Oh, yes. I look on it as happy times and it was a 
big blow to me when she went. I lost my best friend, and she was 73.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you were still with them in those years after the War, did you ever have a holiday with them? Go away at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, I went to Dovercourt, for a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 With the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. We took Gwen, you see. Used to take her out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you stay in a boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, loved it. I used to get up at 7 o'clock and go and get the hot rolls for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How did you spend the day? On the beach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
Yes, with Gwenyth, on the sand. Or sometimes Mrs. Newman would say, 'bring Gwenyth in Catherine, and you can go and have a look at the shops, if you like'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And she'd look after her, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She'd look after Gwen while I'd gone, yes. Or we'd all go out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, I was going to ask you. Did you also have a supper in the evening, about 9?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, we always had supper. Sometimes the peas were fresh out - 'Catherine, will you cook me some peas tonight?' Yes
, yes, cook some peas, or we'd bring some - we'd go down to Brightlingsea and get some fish and chips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What would you have with the peas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, sometimes they'd have sausages, or \{BLANK\} do that. Sometimes we'd have egg and chips. Or 'what are you
 frying, Catherine?' I said, 'you'll have some in the morning, dear'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you were with the foster parents I think you said they would have their hot meal at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, at 5 o'clock, after 5 o'clock because he'd had no hot dinner. She used to 
give him meat sandwiches. She looked after him, I will say that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 
But the hot meal they used to have it together because we went to school, so we came home to rise, boiled rice on a cold day and milk, hot milk, with the toasted cheese, you see, and then we had a hot tea, as well, something with pudding,}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Roly Poly pudding, and meat and potatoes and another veg.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And that would be about 5, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And also supper before you went to bed, later, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, nothing to eat before we went to bed. We had milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But you had a hot tea so you didn't need it, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Children don't need it, do they? The kitchen stove was let out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you had your night out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes. They didn't keep that going here at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 Newman's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 , so that when
 I got in I'd knock on the door, you see, because I knew it was suppertime, I'd got to set the supper. So I'd set the supper and when I'd set it Mrs. Newman would say, 'Catherine, don't sit out there in the cold. Come sit in here, bring your supper in her
e with us. Don't sit out there'. See, they were nice, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 So in the evenings you sat in the ... was it the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 used to sit in there from the fire until they told me to. 'Let your kitchen fire out and come in here and eat with us, Catherine', you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you have your own bedroom to yourself there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, yes, nice little bedroom. Very nice little bedroom. Over the kitchen, it was warm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Were there a lot of fires to see to in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, there was .
.. we kept 3 going, you see. And the kitchen, that was always going because it heated the water, that was the ... none of this central heating was out then. It was Rayburn, and heated all the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When you were with your foster parents, did your foster father do anything in the home in the way of work, household...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, he never did a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And in the garden? Did he do the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Well, he hired a piece of ground because they'd got no garden and he used to do that, dig it, and that,
 and he grew plenty of vegetables and I used to take it round the green as a little girl, cauliflowers a penny each, and sell them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you like doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I'd got to do it whether I wanted to do it or not. But I used to be pleased, you know, 
to think I'd come home with an empty basket. Same as I used to say to Mrs. Wright, 'empty basket, I've sold all the butter', I used to be so pleased. But Father did, he used to sell his vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Going round? He didn't have a stall, he used to take them round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, I used to take ...they'd come down and order them, and I used to take them on Saturday morning. I was away from school and I could take them, then, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did she bake her own bread, the foster mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, she didn't,
 but the neighbour did next door and I used to take her bread to the bakery in a pram in a white table cloth. 'Please would you bake this bread for Mrs. Taylor, and what time shall I come for it?' and he'd say, 'well, come about half past 3'. And I used t
o go and get it and she'd give me a little loaf she'd made especially for me for taking it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 She didn't pay you anything, that was your reward was it? The little loaf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, but she had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  pence a week for doing her errands, and that, as I said ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The previous time, yes. And was there anything else like bottling or preserving that your foster mother did? Did she make jam at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, she used to make jam, and sugar then was cheap, you see and the fruit, you could go and get the blackberrie
s they were given to you, nearly. The same about corn. We used to go into the fields in August, the harvest, and pick up the ears of corn. You could go after the machine had taken all the corn up, that couldn't pick the short little ears up, you see, and 
they were left. Well rather than they be wasted the farmer would let you go and what they call \{BLANK\}
 Well, she made me a little bag, they would put the short ears in ... we all had one, we all ... her boy and herself and, oh, no end of people went and pic
ked the ears up and the long ears, of course, they bunched. And they took it all, armfuls, sacks, and they took it home and the next day they took it to the millers - the mill is pulled down now - to be ground for flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you watch while it was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, we used to leave it, then go and get it the next day. That's the mill and that's the ... where the nursing home was, where Mr. Wright lives now. Well that was the mill, now it's pulled down. But I used to take it in a cart, in a hand cart, and
 they used to grind it into flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 How much flour would you get out of your little bundle of sheaves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 A sack of flour was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 all they got. They kept going back as }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 much as they could get. And the farmers were glad of you to do it, to pick it up. It was given to you, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she do anything like pea-picking, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, she didn't go to work like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 But she did do the gleaning and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 get the flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was all? She didn't work outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, no, no. We'd go blackberrying, because Father had a horse and cart. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 
He was a thatcher by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 trade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 , really, and he used to go to different farms to thatch the stacks, and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 We used to go and meet him, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7479491\charrsid10629010 blackberrying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  and then we'd get a ride home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did she make anything out of the blackberries, or did you just eat them fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, she made them jam. Made jam. You see, you got the blackberries for nothing and you got your sugar }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  farthings a lb. 'Cos there was nothing like this preserving sugar then, it was g
ranulated, and moist, or demerara. Those 3 things. Well, we used to use the granulated and that was only a penny halfpenny. Demerara's a penny 3, and moist was a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 When was the last time you remember people going gleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, my dear, it was years ago, before the War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Before that first War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 The last War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 It went on after the First World War, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Wait a minute, no. I should say that stopped at the First War. The First War, I think, not the Second War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But did you do anything in that time like pea-picking or any of that sort of agricultural work, beside the gleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Never. Never went in the fields, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That was in the time before 1918 when you were helping there, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 That would be when I worked there, yes, lived with the Newman family, yes, I used to do the
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And would you still be teaching Sunday School then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I did. Taught in Sunday School }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010  years, I did, and we had the ministers to dinner Sundays, nearly every other Sunday, and tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 A different minister, I suppose, 'cos they
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, yes, 'cos the Chapel always have different ... they didn't stick to the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Did you enjoy meeting the ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, it was nice, yes, yes. Got to know them and like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And what about the anniversaries, what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Oh, we all had new dresses then. Oh, when I went to school, oh, we all had new dresses. It's the only time I eve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212446\charrsid10629010 r had a new dress. And a new hat. I c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 an remember as if it were yesterday, yes. New hat and new dress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 And did you have recitations and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, I always used to recite, and we used to sing, Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 What sort of recitations did you do? Were they very long ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9506902\charrsid10629010 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
 or 6 verses, or 4, about the robin, or the birds, and that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Would you have a tea, as well, at the Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
No, not anniversaries. We never had teas. Treat, we had a treat tea. We went down to the seaside every year, mostly Walton because the beach is better there. That isn't stony, it's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6030301\charrsid10629010 softer}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 . And we used to go to Walton. And then ... before then, we used to march down to the ... there's a field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 In the village was there any friction or feeling when you were young between the Methodist and the Church of England people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 I've never known any. I've never known any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Everyone got on well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, they all got on well, yes. There was nothing of that, now. But they're thinking of joining up, aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 But it was a good community, Bentley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Yes, it always has been. Really, this has always been a place like that, there's never been much ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid462989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 Friction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid274882 CB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 No, not in Gt. Bentley.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-461\li461\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid462989 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \deleted\revauthdel1\revdttmdel1185176131\insrsid8916146\charrsid10629010 
\par }}